Then triangles $PAQ,$ $PBQ,$ and $PCQ$ are all right triangles.  By the Pythagorean theorem,
\begin{align*}
PA &= \sqrt{PQ^2 + AQ^2} = \sqrt{4 + 9} = \sqrt{13}, \\
PB &= \sqrt{PQ^2 + BQ^2} = \sqrt{4 + 9} = \sqrt{13}, \\
PC &= \sqrt{PQ^2 + CQ^2} = \sqrt{4 + 9} = \sqrt{13}.
\end{align*}Also, $\angle APB = \angle BPC = \angle CPA = 90^\circ,$ so triangles $APB,$ $BPC,$ and $CPA$ are all congruent to each other.  Let $T$ be the area of one of these triangles.  Then the total area of the four triangular faces is $4T.$

