By Heron's formula, the area of triangle $ABC$ is
\[T = \sqrt{s(s - 6)(s - 6)(s - 6)},\]where $s = \frac{6 + 6 + 6 \sqrt{2}}{2} = 3 + 3 \sqrt{2}.$  Hence,
\[4T = 4 \sqrt{s(s - 6)(s - 6)(s - 6)} = \boxed{54 + 36 \sqrt{2}}.\]

