Let $O$ be the center of the inscribed circle.  We draw radii from $O$ to $AB,$ $BC,$ and $CA.$

[asy]
import olympiad; import geometry; size(150); defaultpen(linewidth(0.8));
draw((sqrt(3),0)--origin--(0,1)--cycle);
real r1 = (sqrt(3) - 1)/2;
draw(Circle((r1,r1),r1));
label("$A$",(sqrt(3),0),SE);
label("$B$",(0,1),NW);
label("$C$",(0,0),SW);
draw(rightanglemark((0,1),origin,(1,0),3));
label(scale(0.8)*"$60^\circ$",(0,0.9),SE);
draw((r1,r1)--(r1,0));
draw((r1,r1)--(0,r1));
draw((r1,r1)--(sqrt(3)/2,sqrt(3)/2));
label("$O$",(r1,r1),NE);
draw(rightanglemark((r1,0),(r1,r1),(0,r1),3));
draw(rightanglemark((0,r1),(r1,r1),(sqrt(3)/2,sqrt(3)/2),3));
[/asy]

Then $\angle AOB = 120^\circ,$ so $\triangle AOB$ is equilateral, and $AB = 6 \sqrt{3}.$  Thus, the answer is $\boxed{6 \sqrt{3}}$ centimeters.
